# AUD-047 — Symfony Secrets Vault (apps/api/config/secrets/<env>/).
# The vault is SAFE to commit by design EXCEPT the private decryption key:
#   - <env>.encrypt.public.php  → committed (anyone can ADD a secret)
#   - <env>.list.php            → committed (names of stored secrets)
#   - <NAME>.<HASH>.php          → committed (AES-encrypted ciphertext)
#   - <env>.decrypt.private.php → NEVER committed (decrypts everything)
# The decryption key is injected at deploy time via the SYMFONY_DECRYPTION_SECRET
# env var (base64 of the key file), so prod does not need the file on disk at all.
# A repo-wide `secrets/` ignore previously swallowed the whole vault — scope the
# ignore to the private key only so the rest of the vault can be tracked.
**/config/secrets/**/*.decrypt.private.php
# Any other top-level `secrets/` dir (legacy local-secret dumps) stays ignored,
# but NOT the Symfony vault under config/secrets/.
/secrets/

